[2 bladen][blad 1, recto] Selection from Bruges. Reproductions Witt Library [...] [blad 1, verso] Ad [Addendum] 5. Adoration after Brussels: 1) Adoration, Pennsylvania Mus. Philadelphia, copy after Brussels, canvas, 4 repr. from Connoisseur Sept. 1925, Brussels: High horizon like Peasant Wedding; 2) Ph Public Library Arbroath; 3) Von Nemes, Sale München Helbing, 2-3 Nov.1933, N° 29 (vormals Kilény) B'pest; ; [blad 2, recto] Witt Library 4) After Adoration Brussels, Paris Sale Drouot, 15-12-1937, N° 46; 5) Ph (old poor photographs) Monasterio de Las Descalzas Reales, Madrid 125 x 165 cm, Franciscan Exhib. Madrid 1926 [...]; 6) copy Antwerp Museum; [blad 2, verso] The Census of B. Numbering at Bethlehem, Huybrechts Sale, Antwerp, May 1902, N°3, signed and dated bottom right 1566, ex. coll. van Colen de Bouchot, 1892, Panel, 113 x 163. The original? Ph. of detail of Brussels Mus. [onleesbaar]. House on left with the people, Prince Paul of Yugoslavia, from Les Beaux Arts, 9 Nov. 1935, p. 31.
